      "author": "joeyuping",
      "description": "#15 A minor change to how auto-complete bracket works. It now fires only when followed by the $ symbol, space, tab or nothing. In another word, when inserting bracket right before an existing expression, this function will ignore and only adds the open bracket.\r\n\r\ne.g.  (cursor at | location)\r\n|2+1    --->    (2+1    instead of     ()2+1\r\n\r\nThanks @infinityiowastaken for bringing up this issue~",
      "draft": false,
      "name": "1.5.3",
      "prerelease": false,
      "publishedAt": "2021-11-11T02:20:24Z",
      "tag": "1.5.3"
    },
    {
      "assets": [
        {
          "name": "main.js",
          "size": 160381
        },
        {
          "name": "manifest.json",
          "size": 345
        }
      ],
      "author": "joeyuping",
      "description": "IMPORTANT BUG FIXES! \r\n- there had been a serious error in the previous update that causes autoFraction to stop working. I am really sorry about that! This has been resolved  #14\r\n- system now checks for \"\\sum\" keyword before adding \\limits #13 \r\n- I try tackling the issue by ignoring a shorthand if it is preceeded by an alphabet. eg. \"ta\" is the shorthand for \"\\tau. Typing \"del**ta**\" followed by space will **NOT** trigger the replacement. Having this, I also removed the space following the replacement. #12 \r\n\r\nHuge thanks to @infinityiowastaken @fenjalien for bringingup the issues!  \r\n",
      "draft": false,
      "name": "1.5.2",
      "prerelease": false,
      "publishedAt": "2021-11-10T23:41:49Z",
      "tag": "1.5.2"
    },
